node.text:
How incredible is Siwa Oasis in Egypt? 🇪🇬💙 Apply for a feature following the link in our bio and we will publish your photos in our account: @planetfervor

"Siwa lakes are considered to have healing properties for sinus, skin, and eye conditions, which have allowed the oasis to be promoted as a medical and recreational destination. The water here has a salt concentration of more than 95%."

Tag someone who should see this! 🤯

📽 @flyyestguy
📍 Siwa Oasis, Egypt
🎶 Egyptian Pools - Jinsang

node.text:
Would you drive this? 😅 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting planetfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @planetfervor

This footage was taken in Borneo, the third-largest island in the world and the largest in Asia. Immerse in the Southeast Asia’s Malay Archipelago, is shared by the Malaysian states of Sabah and Sarawak, Indonesian Kalimantan and the tiny nation of Brunei. It’s known for its beaches and ancient, biodiverse rainforest, home to wildlife including orangutans and clouded leopards. In Sabah is 4,095m-tall Mount Kinabalu, the island’s highest peak, and, offshore, the famed dive site Sipadan Island.

📽 @khaiiidiir
📍 Kalimantan, Indonesia
🎶 JayCal PR - Me Llamaste

node.text:
Barcelona from night to day via @world_walkerz. ✨ We can promote your photos in our account. Check the link in our bio for instructions: @planetfervor

Barcelona is a cosmopolitan city in the Mediterranean coast of northeastern Spain, capital of the autonomous community of Catalonia and is known for its unique culture, exquisite cuisine, diverse art and spectacular architecture. 🇪🇸

Save this post if you wanna visit and add these to your bucket list! 📝

𝟭𝟬 𝗕𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗗𝗼 𝗶𝗻 𝗕𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗻𝗮
1. Visit La Sagrada Família.
2. Get amazed by Antoni Gaudí at Casa Batlló.
3. Street food tour at La Boqueria. 
4. Enjoy a getaway at Parc del Laberint d'Horta. 
5. Immerse in the Picasso world at the Picasso Museum.
6. Take a walk at the cosmopolitan street of La Rambla. 
7. Discover traditional Catalan folk music at The Palau de la Música Catalana.
8. Beach day at La Barceloneta beach.
9. Shopping time at Portal del Angel or Passeig de Gracia.
10. Hang out at night in El Born.

Who would you visit this awe-inspiring city with?

📸 @world_walkerz
📍 Barcelona, Spain
